                </h2>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12">
                <div class="embla" data-skip-snaps="true" data-align="center" data-contain-scroll="trimSnaps" data-auto-play-interval="5" data-draggable="true">
                    <div class="embla__viewport">
                        <div class="embla__container mbr-text display-7">
                            
<div class="embla__slide" style="margin-right: 1rem;"><div class="slide-content"><div class="item-wrapper" style="background-color: #6592e6"><div class="item-content"><p class="mbr-light"> After searching for a solution to my business needs, I stumbled upon this design platform. The ease of drag-and-drop functionality drew me in initially, but as I delved deeper, I realized its extensive collection of templates was a game-changer for my bakery's website. Though some elements took a bit of getting used to, the variety and customization options kept me engaged. My only complaint was the occasional lag when saving large images. Overall, a satisfying experience!  - <b><i class="mbr-light">Liam S.</i></b></p></div></div></div></div><div class="embla__slide" style="margin-right: 1rem;"><div class="slide-content"><div class="item-wrapper" style="background-color: #6592e6"><div class="item-content"><p class="mbr-light"> I selected this site creation tool due to its reputation for SEO friendliness, which was paramount for my new blog. However, I did encounter a learning curve regarding the editing tools; at times, the interface seemed cluttered. I appreciated the built-in analytics feature, as it provided insights right from the get-go. My only frustration was the limited free options, necessitating a paid plan for full functionality. Yet, the investment was worth it for my online visibility!  - <b><i class="mbr-light">Emma H.</i></b></p></div></div></div></div><div class="embla__slide" style="margin-right: 1rem;"><div class="slide-content"><div class="item-wrapper" style="background-color: #6592e6"><div class="item-content"><p class="mbr-light"> Opting for this design solution stemmed from recommendations by colleagues. The social media integration was seamless, allowing us to showcase our projects effortlessly. I did have questions regarding file upload size limits, which took some research to resolve. The positives definitely outweighed the negatives; I loved the responsive design capabilities, enabling our site to adapt beautifully across devices. However, the customer support response time was slower than I had hoped.  - <b><i class="mbr-light">Sophia T.</i></b></p></div></div></div></div><div class="embla__slide" style="margin-right: 1rem;"><div class="slide-content"><div class="item-wrapper" style="background-color: #6592e6"><div class="item-content"><p class="mbr-light"> After evaluating several options, I chose this website development program primarily for its extensive widget library. As a musician, I required audio player integration, and this platform provided just that, along with great design flexibility. A few questions arose around the custom coding elements, but the tutorials were very informative. My biggest takeaway was the streamlined publishing process, although I faced some challenges with the export features. In all, it’s been a good tool for my online portfolio.  - <b><i class="mbr-light">Noah J.</i></b></p></div></div></div></div><div class="embla__slide" style="margin-right: 1rem;"><div class="slide-content"><div class="item-wrapper" style="background-color: #6592e6"><div class="item-content"><p class="mbr-light"> I turned to this digital creation platform after hearing about its e-commerce capabilities, vital for my online store. It didn’t take long to set up my product listings, and the payment gateway integration was a breeze. However, I encountered some hurdles while trying to customize my checkout process, leading to several questions regarding payment functionalities. The ease of access to customer favorites and reviews was impressive, though the template pool could use more variety. Overall, the positives outweigh the negatives, especially for someone new to online retail!  - <b><i class="mbr-light">Olivia R.</i></b></p></div></div></div></div>

<div class="embla__slide" style="margin-right: 1rem;"><div class="slide-content"><div class="item-wrapper" style="background-color: #6592e6"><div class="item-content"><p class="mbr-light"> Using Mobirise, I built my portfolio site in no time. The drag-and-drop interface made adding sections a breeze, and integrating social media links was seamless. While I struggled with image optimization at first, the platform's templates guided me to achieve a sleek, professional look. - <b><i class="mbr-light">Laura S.</i></b></p></div></div></div></div>
<div class="embla__slide" style="margin-right: 1rem;"><div class="slide-content"><div class="item-wrapper" style="background-color: #6592e6"><div class="item-content"><p class="mbr-light"> I used a different program to create an e-commerce site, but I kept running into compatibility issues with plugins. Eventually, I migrated to Mobirise, where everything felt more integrated. The challenges with payment gateways were minimized thanks to the built-in options. I ended up launching ahead of schedule! - <b><i class="mbr-light">James T.</i></b></p></div></div></div></div>
<div class="embla__slide" style="margin-right: 1rem;"><div class="slide-content"><div class="item-wrapper" style="background-color: #6592e6"><div class="item-content"><p class="mbr-light"> After trying various platforms, I settled on Adobe Dreamweaver. Although it offered robust features, I found it quite complicated. A challenge arose when I wanted to adapt my design for mobile; learning CSS frameworks was daunting. Eventually, I conquered it and my site looks great on all devices! - <b><i class="mbr-light">Ella G.</i></b></p></div></div></div></div>
<div class="embla__slide" style="margin-right: 1rem;"><div class="slide-content"><div class="item-wrapper" style="background-color: #6592e6"><div class="item-content"><p class="mbr-light"> I ventured into creating a blog using WordPress. The vast array of themes overwhelmed me initially, and I faced hurdles understanding the customization options. However, after picking a minimalist theme, I achieved a clean design, enhanced readability, and it felt like my voice truly shined through. - <b><i class="mbr-light">Oliver H.</i></b></p></div></div></div></div>
<div class="embla__slide" style="margin-right: 1rem;"><div class="slide-content"><div class="item-wrapper" style="background-color: #6592e6"><div class="item-content"><p class="mbr-light"> Building my company website with Wix was a journey filled with learning curves. I had trouble with SEO settings at first, but after research, I optimized my site’s visibility significantly. The analytics tools provided insights that helped me tweak my design and content for better engagement. - <b><i class="mbr-light">Sophia R.</i></b></p></div></div></div></div>

                        
